text:
Some good perspective from Keith on having a loss when the goal is ultimately to go undefeated.

I remember in 1985 the Bears just simply had no answer for one game, Dan Marino and the Dolphins.   

Miami even scored on a pass that bounced off of Dan Hampton's helmet.  Sometimes, the setup is just where things go wrong.

It was their only blemish on the season.

